diet%2C%20meditation%2C%20and%20encouraging%20students%20to%20focus%20on%20their%20%26quot%3Binner%20world.%26quot%3B%20Jobs%20was%20introduced%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsteve-jobs-zen-meditation-buddhism-2015-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EZen%20Buddhism%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20meditation%20in%20the%201970s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJobs%20wrote%20down%20several%20anecdotes%20in%20emails%20to%20himself%20before%20settling%20on%20his%20final%20choices%20for%20the%20speech.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20May%201%20draft%2C%20Jobs%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3BTry%20to%20always%20surround%20yourself%20with%20people%20smarter%20than%20you.%26quot%3B%20They%20can%20come%20from%20different%20walks%20of%20life.%20He%20pointed%20to%20a%20%26quot%3Bterribly%20old%26quot%3B%20engineer%20he'd%20hired%20at%20Apple%20not%20long%20after%20it%20started%2C%20who%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bgenius.%26quot%3B%20(The%20engineer%20was%20in%20his%2040s%20at%20the%20time%2C%20while%20Jobs%20was%2050%20when%20he%20delivered%20the%20speech.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJobs%20ultimately%20chose%20three%20other%20personal%20stories.%20The%20first%20was%20about%20%26quot%3Bconnecting%20the%20dots%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20second%20covered%20%26quot%3Blove%20and%20loss%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20third%20was%20about%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%20oldest%20email%20published%2C%20however%2C%20Jobs%20had%20his%20opener%20locked%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20the%20closest%20I've%20ever%20come%20to%20graduating%20from%20college%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22youtube%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FjiHZqamCD8c%3Ffeature%3Doembed%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Steve%20Jobs%20-%202005%20Stanford%20Commencement%20Address%20(Enhanced%20to%20HD%2F1080p)%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ccc0f58d-aaa8-499a-bf8d-f025a53c86e4%5C%22%3EJobs%20drew%20on%20an%20earlier%20commencement%20address%20and%20mused%20on%20parenting%20in%20his%20notes%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Stanford%20speech%20echoed%20Jobs'%20commencement%20address%20almost%2010%20years%20earlier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201996%2C%20Jobs%20spoke%20to%20the%20graduating%20class%20of%20Palo%20Alto%20High%20School.%20Both%20speeches%20discussed%20intuition%2C%20morality%2C%20and%20following%20one's%20passions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%201996%20speech%20focused%20on%20the%20students%2C%20Jobs%20also%20thought%20about%20the%20parents%20in%20the%20crowd.%20Scribbled%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20a%20printout%20of%20the%20speech%2C%20he%20jotted%20down%20some%20thoughts%20on%20parenting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20tell%20you%20that%20you%20will%20love%20your%20kids%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20handwritten%20notes%20read%2C%20%26quot%3Bnever%20mention%20that%20you%20will%20fall%20in%20love%20with%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20wrote%20that%20%26quot%3Bevery%20injury%20or%20setback%20parents%20feel%2010x%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20they%20will%20always%20see%20their%20children%20as%20they%20were%20at%20ages%205%2C%206%2C%20or%207.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20speech%20concluded%20by%20encouraging%20the%20high%20school%20students%20to%20live%20their%20lives%20with%20as%20few%20regrets%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Stanford%20address%2C%20Jobs%20also%20implored%20the%20students%20to%20find%20what%20they%20love%20and%20live%20each%20day%20like%20it%20was%20their%20last%2C%20telling%20the%20story%20of%20his%20first%20bout%20of%20cancer.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsteve-jobs-death%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EThe%20Apple%20cofounder%20died%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20pancreatic%20cancer%20in%202011%20at%20the%20age%20of%2056.%20On