ps%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2Ffeatured-img-30_11zon-1749794565.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2Ffeatured-img-30_11zon-1749794565-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2Ffeatured-img-30_11zon-1749794565-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2Ffeatured-img-30_11zon-1749794565-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2Ffeatured-img-30_11zon-1749794565-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-448706%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Miyawaki%20planting%20method%2C%20trees%20are%20planted%20closely%20together%2C%20which%20encourages%20competition%20and%20faster%20growth.%20Picture%20source%3A%20Catch%20Foundation%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMiyawaki%20technique%3A%20This%20is%20a%20method%20of%20rapidly%20creating%20dense%2C%20native%20forests%20in%20small%20urban%20or%20rural%20spaces.%20Developed%20by%20Japanese%20botanist%20Dr%20Akira%20Miyawaki%2C%20it%20involves%20planting%20a%20mix%20of%20native%20tree%20and%20shrub%20species%20very%20close%20together%2C%20which%20encourages%20faster%20growth%20and%20dense%20vegetation.%20It%20mimics%20natural%20forest%20ecosystems%20and%20typically%20results%20in%20a%20self-sustaining%2C%20biodiverse%20green%20space%20within%20two%20to%20three%20years%20%E2%80%94%2010%20times%20faster%20and%2030%20times%20denser%20than%20traditional%20afforestation%20methods.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20drove%20this%20change%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20This%20act%20is%20a%20commitment%20to%20a%20better%20future.%20Their%20effort%20from%20four%20years%20ago%20has%20created%20a%20forest-like%20environment%20in%20urban%20areas.%20It%20improved%20air%20quality%20along%20with%20the%20scener