il%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20heart%20of%20petrichor%20is%20a%20tiny%20but%20powerful%20molecule%20called%20%3Cstrong%3Egeosmin%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20Produced%20by%20soil-dwelling%20bacteria%20called%20%3Cem%3EStreptomyces%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20geosmin%20is%20released%20as%20these%20bacteria%20break%20down%20dead%20plants%20and%20organic%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20rain%20hits%20the%20soil%2C%20geosmin%20molecules%20hitch%20a%20ride%20on%20microscopic%20droplets%20that%20bounce%20up%20from%20the%20ground%20and%20float%20into%20the%20air%E2%80%94straight%20into%20our%20noses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%3Cins%20data-ad-slot%3D%5C%229253875046%5C%22%20data-ad-client%3D%5C%22ca-pub-5691287967087057%5C%22%20data-ad-format%3D%5C%22fluid%5C%22%20data-ad-layout%3D%5C%22in-article%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%E2%80%99s%20remarkable%20is%20just%20how%20sensitive%20we%20are%20to%20this%20scent.%20Humans%20can%20detect%20geosmin%20at%20concentrations%20as%20low%20as%205%20parts%20per%20trillion%E2%80%94like%20spotting%20a%20single%20grain%20of%20rice%20in%20an%20entire%20stadium%20of%20people.%20That%20slightly%20metallic%2C%20earthy%20note%20you%20get%20from%20fresh%20beetroots%3F%20That%E2%80%99s%20geosmin%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EWhat%20happens%20when%20rain%20hits%20the%20ground%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%E2%80%99s%20where%20physics%20joins%20the%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20a%20raindrop%20lands%2C%20especially%20on%20dry%20ground%2C%20it%20traps%20tiny%20air%20bubbles%20beneath%20its%20surface.%20These%20bubbles%20rise%2C%20burst%2C%20and%20launch%20the%20geosmin%20and%20plant%20oils%20into%20the%20air%20in%20microscopic%20sprays.%20It%E2%80%99s%20like%20nature%E2%80%99s%20own%20champagne%20fizz%E2%80%94only%20it%E2%80%99s%20the%20soil%20releasing%20its%20hidden%20fragrances.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%3Cins%20data-ad-slot%3